    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1867-05-27T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1867-05-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="283"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d283">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Plumb</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Seward</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New Orleans,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1867-05-27">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 27, 1867</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: At 9 o’clock last evening, I received the
                    following telegraphic despatch from Mr. Marshall, the consul at Matamoros:</p>
                <p rend="center">[Via Galveston, May 26. Dated Matamoros, May 21, 1867.]</p>
                <p>To <hi rend="smallcaps">E. L. Plumb,</hi>
                    <hi rend="italic">St. Charles Hotel, New Orleans:</hi>
                </p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to transmit to you the following
                    official letter:</p>
                <p rend="right">“<hi rend="smallcaps">San Louis Potosi,</hi>
                    <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 15.</p>
                <p>“General <hi rend="smallcaps">Berriozabal</hi>:</p>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">“My Esteemed Friend</hi>: Viva la patria!! Queretaro has
                    fallen by force of arms this a. m. at 8 o’clock. Maximilian, Mejia, Castillo,
                    and Miramon are prisoners.</p>
                <p rend="right">“BENITO JUAREZ.”</p>
                <p>Yours, truly,</p>
                <p rend="right">M.B. MARSHALL.</p>
                <p>The importance of the news it contained led me to transmit the despatch to you at
                    once by telegraph, as received.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, with the highest respect, your most obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>E. L. PLUMB.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward,</hi>
                        <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State, Washington, D. C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
